You have 3 options if you want mixin behaviour:<p>- Use old syntax or explicitly add mixin to prototype
- Use composition. A bit annoying, because you have to make an extra class<p><pre><code>    class OuterComponent extends React.Component {
      render() {
        return (
          <MixinComponent>
            <InnerComponent />
          </MixinComponent>
        );
      }
    }

    class InnerComponent extends React.Component{}
</code></pre>
- wait for decorators (?)

I disagree that a signed type is the correct solution to that, rather you need a while loop:<p><pre><code>  std::size_t i = foo.size();
  while (i != 0) {
    --i;
    ...
  }</code></pre>
